    "what_description": "Thelypteris grima is a species of fern belonging to the family Aspleniaceae, commonly known as the maidenhair ferns. It is a terrestrial fern with a stipe length of 20-45 cm and a lamina length of 30-50 cm, exhibiting a deltoid to ovate shape and a bipinnate to tripinnate leaf arrangement. The lamina is glabrous or hairy on the lower surface, with a serrated margin and a pinnate venation pattern. The frond is attached to the rhizome via a stipe with a brown or reddish-brown color, and the leaf segments are linear to lanceolate in shape. The plant produces sporangia in the form of sori on the abaxial surface of the leaflets.",
